        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35159",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For archival purposes:\n{quote}For some reason if you use routes, Zend_Navigation will interpret urls that it renders from pages objects according to the route that landed you on the page you're on. This means that menus, breadcrumb, etc. will be parsed with strange URL patterns and presumptiions about controller\/module\/action values as designated in your router. For instance, if I click on a link with admin\/ as a prefix, all my menu items will suddenly have admin\/ as a prefix! \n\nTo un-fuck up your pages, after you've been routed, (i.e., in an action plugin or a view helper) include this snippet:\n        $router = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance()->getRouter();\n        $fake_route = new Zend_Controller_Request_Http();\n        $fake_route->setRequestUri('\/');\n        $router->route($fake_route);\n\nThis will flip the front controller back to the default router.{quote}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-11T11:32:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-11T11:32:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35163",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assigning to Robin. This is actually not so much a router issue as a Zend_Navigation issue; the router is behaving as expected and documented.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-12T04:36:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-12T04:36:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35164",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What's the issue here? Is it the old \"you have to specify route\/module\/controller\/action for each page, otherwise the generated links will be weird\"? If so, that's not a bug. It's just how the URL helper (which in turn uses the route's assemble() method) works.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-12T04:44:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-12T04:44:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35309",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Okay, so I guess this is not an issue anymore.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
